---
description: Mini ERP React project baseline rules
alwaysApply: true
---

This project is a desktop-first mini ERP built with React + TypeScript + Tauri.

Core rules:
- Treat the docs folder as the source of truth before proposing or writing code.
- Read docs/00_README.md first when the task relates to architecture or documentation structure.
- Follow the product, status, validation, navigation, and UI rules from the docs before implementing anything.
- Keep the app enterprise-oriented, desktop-first, and operationally dense.
- Prefer reusable shells and patterns for:
  - sidebar
  - list pages
  - document pages
  - master-data pages
  - form layouts
- Do not invent new business logic when the docs already define it.
- Do not add features outside MVP unless explicitly requested.
- Keep strong TypeScript typing for entities, statuses, props, and UI contracts.
- Prefer small reusable components over large monolithic pages.
- Preserve consistency across all modules.

UI direction:
- Desktop ERP style
- Serious and structured
- Clean dark theme
- Dense but readable
- Strong list/grid UX
- Strong document-page consistency
- Avoid mobile-style patterns unless explicitly requested

Implementation discipline:
- Before coding, inspect relevant docs.
- When working on list pages, follow the list-page and UI consistency docs.
- When working on document pages, follow the document layout and navigation docs.
- When working on statuses and validation, follow the domain/status/validation docs.
- When something is ambiguous, prefer asking for clarification rather than inventing behavior.